{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Chronicles 11 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:1",
      "text": "Then all Israel gathered together to David at Hebron, and said, “Behold, we are your bone and flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:2",
      "text": "In times past, even when Saul was king, it was you that led out and brought in Israel; and the Lord your God said to you, ‘You shall be shepherd of my people Israel, and you shall be prince over my people Israel.’ ”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:3",
      "text": "So all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron; and David made a covenant with them at Hebron before the Lord, and they anointed David king over Israel, according to the word of the Lord by Samuel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:4",
      "text": "And David and all Israel went to Jerusalem, that is Jebus, where the Jebusites were, the inhabitants of the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:5",
      "text": "The inhabitants of Jebus said to David, “You will not come in here.” Nevertheless David took the stronghold of Zion, that is, the city of David.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:6",
      "text": "David said, “Whoever shall smite the Jebusites first shall be chief and commander.” And Joab the son of Zeruiah went up first, so he became chief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:7",
      "text": "And David dwelt in the stronghold; therefore it was called the city of David.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:8",
      "text": "And he built the city round about from the Millo in complete circuit; and Joab repaired the rest of the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:9",
      "text": "And David became greater and greater, for the Lord of hosts was with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:10",
      "text": "Now these are the chiefs of David's mighty men, who gave him strong support in his kingdom, together with all Israel, to make him king, according to the word of the Lord concerning Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:11",
      "text": "This is an account of David's mighty men: Jashobe-am, a Hachmonite, was chief of the three; he wielded his spear against three hundred whom he slew at one time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:12",
      "text": "And next to him among the three mighty men was Eleazar the son of Dodo, the Ahohite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:13",
      "text": "He was with David at Pas-dammim when the Philistines were gathered there for battle. There was a plot of ground full of barley, and the men fled from the Philistines.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:14",
      "text": "But he took his stand in the midst of the plot, and defended it, and slew the Philistines; and the Lord saved them by a great victory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:15",
      "text": "Three of the thirty chief men went down to the rock to David at the cave of Adullam, when the army of Philistines was encamped in the valley of Rephaim.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:16",
      "text": "David was then in the stronghold; and the garrison of the Philistines was then at Bethlehem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:17",
      "text": "And David said longingly, “O that some one would give me water to drink from the well of Bethlehem which is by the gate!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:18",
      "text": "Then the three mighty men broke through the camp of the Philistines, and drew water out of the well of Bethlehem which was by the gate, and took and brought it to David. But David would not drink of it; he poured it out to the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:19",
      "text": "and said, “Far be it from me before my God that I should do this. Shall I drink the lifeblood of these men? For at the risk of their lives they brought it.” Therefore he would not drink it. These things did the three mighty men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:20",
      "text": "Now Abishai, the brother of Joab, was chief of the thirty. And he wielded his spear against three hundred men and slew them, and won a name beside the three.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:21",
      "text": "He was the most renowned of the thirty, and became their commander; but he did not attain to the three.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:22",
      "text": "And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was a valiant man of Kabzeel, a doer of great deeds; he smote two ariels of Moab. He also went down and slew a lion in a pit on a day when snow had fallen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:23",
      "text": "And he slew an Egyptian, a man of great stature, five cubits tall. The Egyptian had in his hand a spear like a weaver's beam; but Benaiah went down to him with a staff, and snatched the spear out of the Egyptian's hand, and slew him with his own spear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:24",
      "text": "These things did Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and won a name beside the three mighty men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:25",
      "text": "He was renowned among the thirty, but he did not attain to the three. And David set him over his bodyguard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:26",
      "text": "The mighty men of the armies were Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:27",
      "text": "Shammoth of Harod, Helez the Pelonite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:28",
      "text": "Ira the son of Ikkesh of Tekoa, Abi-ezer of Anathoth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:29",
      "text": "Sibbecai the Hushathite, Ilai the Ahohite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:30",
      "text": "Maharai of Netophah, Heled the son of Baanah of Netophah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:31",
      "text": "Ithai the son of Ribai of Gibeah of the Benjaminites, Benaiah of Pirathon,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:32",
      "text": "Hurai of the brooks of Gaash, Abiel the Arbathite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:33",
      "text": "Azmaveth of Baharum, Eliahba of Sha-albon,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:34",
      "text": "Hashem the Gizonite, Jonathan the son of Shagee the Hararite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:35",
      "text": "Ahiam the son of Sachar the Hararite, Eliphal the son of Ur,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:36",
      "text": "Hepher the Mecherathite, Ahijah the Pelonite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:37",
      "text": "Hezro of Carmel, Naarai the son of Ezbai,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:38",
      "text": "Joel the brother of Nathan, Mibhar the son of Hagri,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:39",
      "text": "Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai of Be-eroth, the armor-bearer of Joab the son of Zeruiah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:40",
      "text": "Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:41",
      "text": "Uriah the Hittite, Zabad the son of Ahlai,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:42",
      "text": "Adina the son of Shiza the Reubenite, a leader of the Reubenites, and thirty with him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:43",
      "text": "Hanan the son of Maacah, and Joshaphat the Mithnite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:44",
      "text": "Uzzia the Ashterathite, Shama and Je-iel the sons of Hotham the Aroerite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:45",
      "text": "Jedia-el the son of Shimri, and Joha his brother, the Tizite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:46",
      "text": "Eliel the Mahavite, and Jeribai, and Joshaviah, the sons of Elna-am, and Ithmah the Moabite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.11.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 11:47",
      "text": "Eliel, and Obed, and Ja-asiel the Mezoba-ite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
